title: Executive Order 7992-Revocation of Executive Order No. 3674 of May 17, 1922, Withdrawing Lands For the Use and Occupancy of the DuBois Rifle Club For Rifle Practice
content: By virtue of and pursuant to the authority vested in me by the act of June 25, 1910, ch. 421, 36 Stat. 847, as amended by the act of August 24, 1912, ch. 369, 37 Stat. 497, Executive Order No. 3674 of May 17, 1922, withdrawing lands for the use and occupancy of the DuBois Rifle Club, DuBois, Wyoming, for rifle practice, is hereby revoked.
citation: Franklin D. Roosevelt, Executive Order 7992-Revocation of Executive Order No. 3674 of May 17, 1922, Withdrawing Lands For the Use and Occupancy of the DuBois Rifle Club For Rifle Practice Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/368791
